title: Ohio State's Corey Smith out for season with leg injury
text:
Ohio State's Corey Smith out for season with leg injury theScore 3 hrs ago © Joe Maiorana-USA TODAY Sports Ohio State has lost another wide receiver, as Corey Smith is out for the rest of the year with a leg injury, head coach Urban Meyer announced Monday.
AdChoices Smith is the second Buckeyes receiver to be put on the season-ending injured list, joining Noah Brown , who broke his leg in training camp.
In four games, Smith has five receptions for 62 yards, and although he's a senior, Meyer said there's a chance he'll look for an extra year of eligibility.
